text_answer.content: The Analyzing Information question should perhaps be rewritten. It asks "what happened in Room 23 after the happiness class started" Choices A, B, and C all happened AFTER the class started. While I understand the answer, this will be confusing to a 5th grader because any of the first three choices happened after the class started, and choices A and B actually occurred before the correct answer choice C. This question needs to be more specific. As far as Multiple Meaning Words...once again....we are asking for the meaning of the word light (which I already commented is used on way too many stories). IN this instance, the correct answer choice A states "to brighten or illuminate (as used in the story)". DON'T add the part in parentheses! We want the student to figure out what it means, we don't want to TELL them. We can't give them hints in parentheses. And we need to change up the words we use in Multiple Meaning Words.
